# <type>(p<package>/s<session>): <subject>
#
# Body: why, not what. Wrap at 72 chars. Leave a blank line above.
#
# Footer: references (e.g. "Refs: D11", "Closes: P1/S1").
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore, build, ci, perf, revert
# Scope: package/session, e.g. p1/s1, p3/s2. Use a broader scope only when
#        the change spans multiple packages.
#
# Examples:
#   feat(p1/s1): scaffold repo with charter, gitignore, env example
#   docs(p1/s1): record D11 incremental scaffold decision
#   chore(p2/s4): pin keycloak image to 26.0
#
# Reminders:
# - Schema changes must update docs/charter/schema.md in the same commit.
# - New observability metrics require a documented decision they inform.
